except Exception as e:

def predict(CRIM, ZN, INDUS, CHAS, NOX, RM, AGE, DIS, RAD, TAX, PTRATIO, B, LSTAT):
    "Output: var1"
    result = None
    try:
        global _compile_error
        if _compile_error is not None:
            raise _compile_error

        import numpy as np
        import pandas as pd

        if CRIM == None: CRIM = np.nan
        if ZN == None: ZN = np.nan
        if INDUS == None: INDUS = np.nan
        if CHAS == None: CHAS = np.nan
        if NOX == None: NOX = np.nan
        if RM == None: RM = np.nan
        if AGE == None: AGE = np.nan
        if DIS == None: DIS = np.nan
        if RAD == None: RAD = np.nan
        if TAX == None: TAX = np.nan
        if PTRATIO == None: PTRATIO = np.nan
        if B == None: B = np.nan
        if LSTAT == None: LSTAT = np.nan
        inputarray = np.array([CRIM,ZN,INDUS,CHAS,NOX,RM,AGE,DIS,RAD,TAX,PTRATIO,B,LSTAT]).reshape((1, -1))
        column = ["CRIM","ZN","INDUS","CHAS","NOX","RM","AGE","DIS","RAD","TAX","PTRATIO","B","LSTAT"]
        inputrun = pd.DataFrame(data=inputarray, columns=column)
        result = obj.predict(inputrun)
        if result.size == 1:
            result = np.asscalar(result)
    except Exception as e:

        if result is None:
            result = tuple(None for i in range(1))
    return result
